nited States Code.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In subsection (a)(5) and (7), the words “prescribed . . . issued” are added for consistency in the revised title and with other titles of the Code.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In subsection (a)(5), the words “of the Secretary of Transportation” are omitted as surplus.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In subsection (a)(6), the words “proclaimed by the President” are omitted as surplus. The words “section 3 of the International Navigational Rules Act of 1977 (","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t33/s1602"},"text":"33 U.S.C. 1602","children":[],"tail":")” are substituted for “"},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t33/s143"},"text":"section 143 of title 33","children":[],"tail":"” because the section was part of the Act of "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1951-10-11"},"text":"October 11, 1951","children":[],"tail":" (ch. 495, "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/65/406"},"text":"65 Stat. 406","children":[],"tail":"), that was repealed by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1963-09-24/s3"},"text":"section 3 of the Act of September 24, 1963","children":[],"tail":" ("},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/88/131"},"text":"Public Law 88–131","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/77/194"},"text":"77 Stat. 194","children":[],"tail":"), and replaced by 33:ch. 21. Chapter 21 was repealed by section 10 of the International Navigational Rules Act of 1977 ("},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/95/75"},"text":"Public Law 95–75","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/91/311"},"text":"91 Stat. 311","children":[],"tail":") and replaced by 33:1601–1608."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In subsection (a)(7), the words “holding . . . such certificate” are omitted because of the restatement.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In subsection (a)(8), the words “by the Administrator” are omitted as surplus.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"In subsection (b), the word “Administrator” in section 610(b) of the Federal Aviation Act of 1958 (","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/85/726"},"text":"Public Law 85–726","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/72/780"},"text":"72 Stat. 780","children":[],"tail":") is retained on authority of 49:106(g). The words “to the extent, and . . . and conditions” and “by such airmen” are omitted as surplus."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"historicalAndRevision","id":"idcc004dae-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/103/429"},"text":"Pub. L. 103–429","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"This amends 49:44711(a)(2)(B), (5), and (7) and 46310(b) to correct erroneous cross-references.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idcc004daf-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"idcc004db0-47c4-11f1-9671-b5c725212f70"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2024—Subsec. (a)(10), (11). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/118/63"},"text":"Pub. L. 118–63","children":[],"tail":" added par. (10) and redesignated former par. (10) as (11)."}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"2020—Subsec. (d). ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/116/260"},"text":"Pub. L. 116–260","children":[],"tail":" amended subsec. (d) generally. 